{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H9pmZ3Wspy3SB5UNKEybL9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 4.4: Source Isolation Enforcement\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want source_access: false enforced via source-free workspace,\n9\tso that the evaluator cannot access implementation code.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a `source-isolation.ts` module at `src/lib/source-isolation.ts`\n14\t   **When** inspected\n15\t   **Then** it exports a `createIsolatedWorkspace(options: IsolationOptions): Promise<IsolatedWorkspace>` function that creates a temp directory at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/` with a `story-files/` subdirectory\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** a task with `source_access: false` and a list of story file paths\n19\t   **When** `createIsolatedWorkspace()` is called with `{ runId, storyFiles }` \n20\t   **Then** the temp directory is created, story files are copied into `story-files/`, and a `verdict/` directory is created for evaluator output\n21\t   **And** the workspace directory does NOT contain `src/`, `node_modules/`, `package.json`, or any source code files\n22\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n23\t\n24\t3. **Given** a created `IsolatedWorkspace`\n25\t   **When** its `toDispatchOptions()` method is called\n26\t   **Then** it returns `DispatchOptions` with `cwd` set to the temp directory path\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t4. **Given** an agent resolved with `disallowedTools` (e.g., the evaluator agent)\n30\t   **When** the subagent definition is compiled via `compileSubagentDefinition()` and source isolation is active\n31\t   **Then** `disallowedTools` includes `[\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` preventing the agent from modifying any files\n32\t   **And** this is verified by checking that the evaluator embedded template at `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` already specifies `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]`\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** an `IsolatedWorkspace` after use\n36\t   **When** `cleanup()` is called\n37\t   **Then** the temp directory and all its contents are removed from disk\n38\t   **And** calling `cleanup()` on an already-cleaned workspace does not throw\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** `createIsolatedWorkspace()` is called with an empty `storyFiles` array\n42\t   **When** the workspace is created\n43\t   **Then** the temp directory and `story-files/` subdirectory still exist (empty)\n44\t   **And** `verdict/` directory exists\n45\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n46\t\n47\t7. **Given** a story file path that does not exist on disk\n48\t   **When** `createIsolatedWorkspace()` attempts to copy it\n49\t   **Then** a warning is logged (via `warn()`) and the missing file is skipped without throwing\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n51\t\n52\t8. **Given** `dispatchAgent()` is called with `DispatchOptions.cwd` pointing to the isolated workspace\n53\t   **When** the Agent SDK `query()` is invoked\n54\t   **Then** the SDK session runs in the temp directory (verified by confirming `agent-dispatch.ts` already passes `options.cwd` to query — line 134)\n55\t   **And** the agent has no access to the original project's `src/` directory\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** unit tests for the source isolation module\n59\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n60\t   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for `source-isolation.ts` covering: workspace creation, story file copying, missing file handling, dispatch options generation, cleanup, idempotent cleanup, and no-source-code verification\n61\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n62\t\n63\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n64\t\n65\t- [x] Task 1: Create source isolation module interfaces (AC: #1, #3)\n66\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/source-isolation.ts`\n67\t  - [x] Define `IsolationOptions` interface: `{ runId: string; storyFiles: string[] }`\n68\t  - [x] Define `IsolatedWorkspace` interface: `{ dir: string; storyFilesDir: string; verdictDir: string; toDispatchOptions(): DispatchOptions; cleanup(): Promise<void> }`\n69\t  - [x] Import `DispatchOptions` from `agent-dispatch.ts` for return type\n70\t\n71\t- [x] Task 2: Implement workspace creation (AC: #1, #2, #6)\n72\t  - [x] Implement `createIsolatedWorkspace(options: IsolationOptions): Promise<IsolatedWorkspace>`\n73\t  - [x] Create temp directory at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/` using `mkdtemp` or `mkdirSync`\n74\t  - [x] Create `story-files/` subdirectory inside the temp dir\n75\t  - [x] Create `verdict/` subdirectory inside the temp dir\n76\t  - [x] Copy each story file from `storyFiles` array into `story-files/`\n77\t  - [x] Handle empty `storyFiles` array — still create directories\n78\t\n79\t- [x] Task 3: Implement missing file handling (AC: #7)\n80\t  - [x] When a story file path doesn't exist, call `warn()` from `output.ts` with a descriptive message\n81\t  - [x] Skip the missing file and continue with remaining files\n82\t  - [x] Do not throw — the workspace is still valid with fewer files\n83\t\n84\t- [x] Task 4: Implement dispatch options and cleanup (AC: #3, #5)\n85\t  - [x] `toDispatchOptions()` returns `{ cwd: dir }` where `dir` is the temp directory path\n86\t  - [x] `cleanup()` removes the temp directory recursively using `rm -rf` / `fs.rm(dir, { recursive: true, force: true })`\n87\t  - [x] `cleanup()` is idempotent — if directory already removed, no error\n88\t\n89\t- [x] Task 5: Verify existing integration points (AC: #4, #8)\n90\t  - [x] Confirm `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml` has `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]` (from story 3-2)\n91\t  - [x] Confirm `agent-dispatch.ts` line 134 already passes `options.cwd` to `query()` (from story 4-1)\n92\t  - [x] Confirm `compileSubagentDefinition()` in `agent-resolver.ts` already passes `disallowedTools` through (line 343)\n93\t  - [x] No changes needed to `agent-dispatch.ts` or `agent-resolver.ts`\n94\t\n95\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #9)\n96\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/source-isolation.test.ts`\n97\t  - [x] Test: `createIsolatedWorkspace()` creates temp dir with expected structure\n98\t  - [x] Test: story files are copied to `story-files/` subdirectory\n99\t  - [x] Test: `src/` directory does NOT exist in isolated workspace\n100\t  - [x] Test: `toDispatchOptions()` returns `{ cwd }` pointing to the temp dir\n101\t  - [x] Test: `cleanup()` removes the temp directory\n102\t  - [x] Test: `cleanup()` called twice does not throw (idempotent)\n103\t  - [x] Test: empty `storyFiles` array creates directories but no files in `story-files/`\n104\t  - [x] Test: missing story file logs a warning and is skipped\n105\t  - [x] Test: `verdict/` directory exists in workspace\n106\t  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on `source-isolation.ts` — achieved 100% across all metrics\n107\t\n108\t## Dev Notes\n109\t\n110\t### Module Design Decision\n111\t\n112\tSource isolation is a standalone `source-isolation.ts` module rather than being added to `agent-dispatch.ts` or `evaluator.ts`. Rationale:\n113\t\n114\t1. `agent-dispatch.ts` is intentionally stateless — it does not do file I/O beyond what the SDK does (per story 4-1 anti-patterns)\n115\t2. The evaluator module (story 6-1) will call `createIsolatedWorkspace()` to set up the blind workspace, then pass the resulting `cwd` to `dispatchAgent()`\n116\t3. Source isolation is a reusable primitive — any task with `source_access: false` uses it, not just the evaluator\n117\t\n118\t### How Source Isolation Works End-to-End\n119\t\n120\t```\n121\tworkflow-engine (story 5-1) checks task.source_access:\n122\t  if source_access === false:\n123\t    1. createIsolatedWorkspace({ runId, storyFiles })\n124\t       -> creates /tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/\n125\t       -> copies story AC files into story-files/\n126\t       -> creates verdict/ for output\n127\t    2. workspace.toDispatchOptions()\n128\t       -> returns { cwd: '/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/' }\n129\t    3. dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, { ...dispatchOptions })\n130\t       -> agent-dispatch passes cwd to SDK query() (already implemented, line 134)\n131\t       -> SDK runs agent in temp dir — no src/ present\n132\t    4. workspace.cleanup()\n133\t       -> removes temp dir\n134\t  else:\n135\t    dispatchAgent(definition, prompt, { cwd: process.cwd() })\n136\t    -> normal dispatch in project directory\n137\t```\n138\t\n139\t### Workspace Structure\n140\t\n141\t```\n142\t/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/\n143\t  story-files/     # ACs and story context — copied from sprint\n144\t  verdict/         # evaluator writes JSON verdict here (used by story 6-1)\n145\t```\n146\t\n147\tThe workspace deliberately omits: `src/`, `node_modules/`, `package.json`, `.git/`, `.codeharness/`, and all other project files. The evaluator sees only what was explicitly placed there.\n148\t\n149\t### Existing Code That Already Supports This\n150\t\n151\t- `agent-dispatch.ts` line 134: `...(options?.cwd ? { cwd: options.cwd } : {})` — already passes cwd to SDK\n152\t- `agent-resolver.ts` line 343: `disallowedTools: agent.disallowedTools ?? []` — already passes through from agent config\n153\t- `templates/agents/evaluator.yaml`: already defines `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]` (from story 3-2)\n154\t- `workflow-parser.ts` line 11: `source_access: boolean` — already parsed from workflow YAML\n155\t\n156\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n157\t\n158\t- Does NOT implement the evaluator itself — that's Epic 6 (story 6-1)\n159\t- Does NOT implement Docker container management — that's Epic 6\n160\t- Does NOT copy observability configs into the workspace — that's Epic 6 (evaluator observability, FR37)\n161\t- Does NOT modify `agent-dispatch.ts` — it already handles `cwd`\n162\t- Does NOT modify `agent-resolver.ts` — it already passes `disallowedTools`\n163\t- Does NOT orchestrate when isolation is used — the workflow-engine (story 5-1) decides based on `task.source_access`\n164\t\n165\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n166\t\n167\t- **Do NOT spawn a git worktree** — too complex, AD2 explicitly chose temp dir for simplicity\n168\t- **Do NOT symlink source files** — defeats isolation purpose\n169\t- **Do NOT use Docker-in-Docker** — AD2 explicitly rejected this\n170\t- **Do NOT add state tracking to this module** — it creates a directory and cleans it up, nothing more\n171\t- **Do NOT import workflow-state** — this module is stateless (the engine records workspace info if needed)\n172\t\n173\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n174\t\n175\t- **Story 4-1** created `agent-dispatch.ts` with `DispatchOptions.cwd` — this module creates the cwd value for isolated dispatch\n176\t- **Story 3-2** created the evaluator embedded template with `disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]` — this module relies on that being set\n177\t- **Story 3-3** created `agent-resolver.ts` with `compileSubagentDefinition()` — this module relies on it passing `disallowedTools` through\n178\t- **Story 2-2** created `workflow-parser.ts` with `source_access` field on `ResolvedTask` — the engine will use this to decide when to invoke isolation\n179\t\n180\t### Project Structure Notes\n181\t\n182\t- New file: `src/lib/source-isolation.ts` — workspace creation, file copying, cleanup\n183\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/source-isolation.test.ts`\n184\t- No modified files — this module is additive only\n185\t- Aligns with architecture pattern: each module in `src/lib/` is one file with co-located test\n186\t\n187\t### Testing Strategy\n188\t\n189\tUnit tests use real file system operations in a temp directory (same pattern as `workflow-state.test.ts`). Tests create a temp project dir with dummy story files, call `createIsolatedWorkspace()`, verify the workspace structure, then call `cleanup()`. No mocking needed — the module does real fs operations and we verify real results.\n190\t\n191\t### References\n192\t\n193\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 4.4: Source Isolation Enforcement]\n194\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD2: Evaluator Workspace Isolation]\n195\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR23 — source_access: false enforcement]\n196\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — DispatchOptions.cwd, line 134]\n197\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — compileSubagentDefinition(), disallowedTools, line 343]\n198\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — ResolvedTask.source_access, line 11]\n199\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-1-agent-dispatch-module-sdk-integration.md — predecessor story]\n200\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-2-session-boundary-management.md — predecessor story]\n201\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/4-3-trace-id-generation-injection.md — predecessor story]\n202\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015fa9nSgrfFKiaFb9ewB3kM","session_id":"02876edc-b40e-4eff-87e1-ceab09778e92","uuid":"2e00554c-2c44-4b74-9f1e-1595262d9771","timestamp":"2026-04-02T21:27:19.505Z"}
